12:45.098 --> 12:46.996
Bertram, why are you

12:46.997 --> 12:48.893
dressed like a waiter

12:45.098 --> 12:48.893
at El Taco Grande?

12:51.396 --> 12:52.731
I'm going to Cabo!

12:52.814 --> 12:54.692
- Tell my mom I'll send her
- a chimichanga.

12:57.861 --> 12:59.801
Bertram, I see Wanda

12:59.802 --> 13:01.740
isn't the easiest person

12:57.861 --> 13:01.740
to be around,

13:01.781 --> 13:03.325
but she's still your mom,

13:03.326 --> 13:04.868
and you can't run away

13:01.781 --> 13:04.868
from your problems.

13:04.909 --> 13:06.411
Maybe not in these sandals,

13:06.412 --> 13:07.912
but I got a change of shoes

13:04.909 --> 13:07.912
in my bag.

13:10.708 --> 13:12.210
Look, I know what

13:12.211 --> 13:13.711
it's like to have problems

13:10.708 --> 13:13.711
with a parent.

13:13.752 --> 13:15.587
My dad was really tough.

13:15.629 --> 13:17.048
In fact, we didn't really

13:17.049 --> 13:18.465
bond until I overcame

13:15.629 --> 13:18.465
that last hurdle.

13:18.507 --> 13:19.717
And what was that?

13:19.758 --> 13:20.759
The last hurdle.

13:20.760 --> 13:21.760
Of the obstacle course.

13:23.470 --> 13:24.638
When I finally cleared it,

13:24.639 --> 13:25.805
he stopped wishing

13:23.470 --> 13:25.805
I was a boy.

13:27.558 --> 13:29.227
I'm glad to hear it.

13:29.228 --> 13:30.894
Meanwhile, I'm in

13:27.558 --> 13:30.894
boarding group A, so, uh...

13:33.397 --> 13:34.649
Bertram,

13:34.650 --> 13:35.899
I know it's my fault

13:33.397 --> 13:35.899
that your mom is here,

13:35.940 --> 13:37.752
- but you might as well
- take advantage of it.

13:37.776 --> 13:39.070
You know, you're right.

13:39.071 --> 13:40.362
It is your fault.

13:42.239 --> 13:44.387
Okay,

13:44.388 --> 13:46.535
we've assigned blame,

13:42.239 --> 13:46.535
let's move on.

13:46.577 --> 13:47.870
My point is, your mom

13:47.871 --> 13:49.162
is not going to be

13:46.577 --> 13:49.162
around forever,

13:49.204 --> 13:51.081
- so you should tell her
- how you feel!

13:51.122 --> 13:52.333
And who's going to tape

13:52.334 --> 13:53.542
her mouth shut

13:51.122 --> 13:53.542
so I can do that?

13:55.168 --> 13:56.587
I'm not going to let you go.

13:56.628 --> 13:58.147
- Oh, yeah?
- How are you gonna stop me?

13:58.171 --> 13:59.172
Is that your passport?

14:00.924 --> 14:02.697
Wha... No! No! Oh!

14:02.698 --> 14:04.469
(SOBBING)

14:07.264 --> 14:08.664
- (MUFFLED)
- You'll thank me later.

14:12.728 --> 14:14.647
I am ashamed I failed

14:14.648 --> 14:16.565
at accomplishing

14:12.728 --> 14:16.565
this scientific task.

14:16.607 --> 14:18.421
Now I know how you feel

14:18.422 --> 14:20.235
when you walk

14:16.607 --> 14:20.235
out of every audition.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.030
Well, I was going to try

14:24.031 --> 14:25.198
and make you feel better,

14:25.240 --> 14:27.040
- but now I'm going to go
- buy a bag of nuts.

14:28.619 --> 14:30.788
I'm so sorry, Jessie.

14:30.829 --> 14:33.312
I am just upset because

14:33.313 --> 14:35.793
Luke has completely cut me

14:30.829 --> 14:35.793
out of our project.

14:35.834 --> 14:37.482
Good luck, Luke!

14:37.483 --> 14:39.129
Break an egg!

14:35.834 --> 14:39.129
(CHUCKLES)

14:39.170 --> 14:40.652
Uh, Jessie, the entire point

14:40.653 --> 14:42.132
of the project is not to

14:39.170 --> 14:42.132
break...

14:42.173 --> 14:43.174
It was a joke!

14:44.635 --> 14:46.303
- Not if you
- have to explain it.

14:51.600 --> 14:53.602
Is it a viscous disaster?

14:57.648 --> 14:59.775
(APPLAUSE)

14:59.817 --> 15:00.900
Ba-boosh!

15:02.653 --> 15:04.029
It actually worked!

15:04.030 --> 15:05.405
Luke succeeded in science.

15:06.406 --> 15:08.408
It is snowing in Hades.

15:10.535 --> 15:12.246
I told you

15:12.247 --> 15:13.955
I had mad scientific skills!

15:13.997 --> 15:15.874
I got us an A!

15:16.792 --> 15:19.043
Congratulations, brother.

15:19.085 --> 15:21.297
When you win the Nobel Prize,

15:21.298 --> 15:23.507
will you at least

15:19.085 --> 15:23.507
invite me to the after-party?

15:23.548 --> 15:25.572
Only if I get a plus one,

15:25.573 --> 15:27.594
and you're

15:23.548 --> 15:27.594
the last person on Earth.

15:27.636 --> 15:29.596
- Thank you, brother!
- (GRUNTS)

15:33.016 --> 15:34.559
- Okay, Luke,
- I'm no Einstein,

15:34.601 --> 15:36.103
But I'm pretty sure

15:36.104 --> 15:37.604
this is a hard-boiled egg.

15:37.646 --> 15:38.919
Hey, the project was

15:38.920 --> 15:40.190
to drop an egg

15:37.646 --> 15:40.190
without breaking it.

15:40.231 --> 15:41.399
And that's what I did.

15:41.441 --> 15:43.276
So you cheated?

15:43.318 --> 15:44.486
No, I thought

15:44.487 --> 15:45.654
outside the box.

15:46.988 --> 15:48.135
Jessie, do you know

15:48.136 --> 15:49.282
what this means?

15:49.324 --> 15:50.347
Yes. Luke is

15:50.348 --> 15:51.368
going to confess.

15:51.409 --> 15:53.016
Which, I'm afraid,

15:53.017 --> 15:54.621
means you're probably

15:51.409 --> 15:54.621
both gonna get an F.

15:54.663 --> 15:57.123
Who gives two soggy samosas?

15:57.165 --> 15:58.980
This means I am

15:58.981 --> 16:00.794
still better than Luke

15:57.165 --> 16:00.794
in science!

16:00.836 --> 16:02.922
Oh, I am happier than

16:02.923 --> 16:05.006
an ion sharing its

16:00.836 --> 16:05.006
valence electron!

16:05.048 --> 16:06.383
I have no idea what

16:06.384 --> 16:07.718
you're talking about.

16:07.759 --> 16:09.177
I know!

16:09.219 --> 16:10.721
(SCREAMING GLEEFULLY)

16:20.230 --> 16:21.356
Thank you.

16:26.277 --> 16:27.362
Jessie, why did you hire

16:27.363 --> 16:28.446
so many waiters?

16:28.488 --> 16:29.782
Oh, I didn't.

16:29.783 --> 16:31.074
They're Bertram's

16:28.488 --> 16:31.074
butler buddies.

16:31.115 --> 16:32.367
I wish they would eat the food

16:32.368 --> 16:33.618
instead of just offering it

16:31.115 --> 16:33.618
to each other.

16:35.495 --> 16:36.622
Thanks for the great party,

16:36.623 --> 16:37.748
Jessie.

16:37.789 --> 16:38.812
Now, if my mother

16:38.813 --> 16:39.833
doesn't show up

16:37.789 --> 16:39.833
to embarrass me,

16:39.875 --> 16:41.585
it'll be perfect.

16:41.626 --> 16:43.254
Bertram, give her a chance.

16:43.255 --> 16:44.880
Maybe she'll surprise you.

16:44.922 --> 16:46.674
After all,

16:46.675 --> 16:48.425
she's older now, and wiser...

16:48.466 --> 16:49.593
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

16:54.723 --> 16:56.246
Happy birthday,

16:56.247 --> 16:57.768
Ber-tootchka!

16:57.809 --> 16:58.810
And she's jumping

16:58.811 --> 16:59.811
out of a cake.

17:01.605 --> 17:02.898
Kill me now.

17:02.940 --> 17:04.357
(BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYING)

17:10.029 --> 17:12.156
- Hey, aren't you guys
- supposed to be dancing, too?

17:12.198 --> 17:14.242
Wanda said we weren't good

17:14.243 --> 17:16.286
enough, so she kicked us

17:12.198 --> 17:16.286
out of the act.

17:16.327 --> 17:18.121
Literally kicked us!

17:18.162 --> 17:20.039
- Those ex-Rockettes
- don't mess around.

17:21.791 --> 17:23.417
I've never been so sad

17:23.419 --> 17:25.044
in a sparkly tutu.

17:26.964 --> 17:28.715
Okay, that's it!

17:28.757 --> 17:30.009
Nobody kicks my kids

17:30.010 --> 17:31.259
out of a gaudy, over the top

17:28.757 --> 17:31.259
dance routine!

17:31.718 --> 17:33.720
(MUSIC STOPS)

17:33.762 --> 17:35.409
Hold it right there,

17:35.410 --> 17:37.056
and on behalf

17:33.762 --> 17:37.056
of that boa, ew!

17:38.266 --> 17:40.018
I'm dancing here!

17:40.059 --> 17:41.874
So? Zuri and Emma

17:41.875 --> 17:43.688
were supposed to

17:40.059 --> 17:43.688
be dancing, too!

17:43.730 --> 17:45.148
- They worked
- really hard at this,

17:45.189 --> 17:46.190
And they were looking

17:46.191 --> 17:47.191
forward to it.

17:47.233 --> 17:48.380
Well, it's not my fault

17:48.381 --> 17:49.527
they can't hack it.

17:50.988 --> 17:52.781
Okay, that is it!

17:52.823 --> 17:54.721
Mom, I'm going to talk,

17:54.722 --> 17:56.618
and for once

17:52.823 --> 17:56.618
you are going to listen!

17:56.660 --> 17:58.287
Okay, gladly,

17:58.288 --> 17:59.913
but right after

17:56.660 --> 17:59.913
my big dance number.

17:59.955 --> 18:02.145
No! I am tired of you

18:02.146 --> 18:04.334
taking over my birthdays

17:59.955 --> 18:04.334
and ruining them!

18:04.375 --> 18:05.836
I don't do that!

18:05.877 --> 18:07.420
Oh, really?

18:07.462 --> 18:08.652
On my sixth birthday,

18:08.653 --> 18:09.840
you canceled the clown

18:09.881 --> 18:11.300
and insisted on doing

18:11.301 --> 18:12.717
your stand-up act.

18:12.759 --> 18:13.885
What's wrong with that?

18:13.927 --> 18:17.096
A, prop comedy is not funny,

18:17.138 --> 18:18.869
and B,

18:18.870 --> 18:20.600
you charged everyone

18:17.138 --> 18:20.600
a two juice box minimum!

18:20.642 --> 18:22.477
That's how they get you.

18:24.021 --> 18:25.481
On my 10th birthday,

18:25.482 --> 18:26.940
you canceled the magician,

18:26.982 --> 18:28.629
and insisted on sawing

18:28.630 --> 18:30.276
me in half yourself.

18:30.318 --> 18:31.820
I still have the scar!

18:33.030 --> 18:34.614
- And we never did find
- Timmy Schwartz

18:34.656 --> 18:36.032
After he stepped into

18:36.033 --> 18:37.408
the Box of Mystery!

18:37.450 --> 18:38.576
He'll turn up.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.662
It was 40 years ago!

18:40.704 --> 18:42.580
- Well,
- get over it already!

18:42.622 --> 18:43.728
I'm sure Timmy has...

18:43.729 --> 18:44.833
Wherever he is!

18:46.793 --> 18:48.441
I can't get over it,

18:48.442 --> 18:50.088
because you keep doing it!

18:50.129 --> 18:51.715
And I let you,

18:51.756 --> 18:53.780
but I draw the line

18:53.781 --> 18:55.802
when you start hurting

18:51.756 --> 18:55.802
the people I love!

18:55.844 --> 18:57.846
What am I, chopped liver?

19:01.725 --> 19:04.227
Just stop shouting at me!

19:04.268 --> 19:05.729
This is why

19:05.730 --> 19:07.188
you're all alone!

19:04.268 --> 19:07.188
(ALL GASP)

19:07.230 --> 19:09.024
Bertram's not alone!

19:09.025 --> 19:10.817
He has us!

19:10.859 --> 19:12.340
Yeah! Even when

19:12.341 --> 19:13.820
he wants to be alone,

19:10.859 --> 19:13.820
we won't let him!

19:15.238 --> 19:17.323
Because he's our best friend!

19:17.365 --> 19:18.722
What other butler would

19:18.723 --> 19:20.077
have a tea party with me?

19:20.118 --> 19:21.307
Or play paintball with me

19:21.308 --> 19:22.495
in the park?

19:22.537 --> 19:23.977
Or listen to my endless,

19:23.978 --> 19:25.415
boring, boyfriend stories?

19:25.456 --> 19:27.000
Or, as I consider them,

19:27.001 --> 19:28.543
cautionary tales.

19:28.585 --> 19:30.378
Or not get mad

19:30.379 --> 19:32.171
when I use him as

19:28.585 --> 19:32.171
a human science experiment?

19:36.134 --> 19:38.095
Thanks, guys.

19:38.136 --> 19:39.513
Ber-tootchka,

19:39.514 --> 19:40.889
why didn't you just tell me

19:38.136 --> 19:40.889
you felt this way?

19:40.931 --> 19:42.266
Well, he tried,

19:42.267 --> 19:43.600
but you started talking

19:40.931 --> 19:43.600
about your gams!

19:43.641 --> 19:45.727
Because they're fantastic!

19:45.769 --> 19:46.854
Who wants to feel?

19:46.855 --> 19:47.938
Come on, kids, line up.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.149
I'm scared again.

19:52.483 --> 19:53.818
Wanda! Focus!

19:56.154 --> 19:57.614
Go ahead, Bertram.

20:00.117 --> 20:01.848
Mom, I love you,

20:01.849 --> 20:03.578
but it can't always

20:00.117 --> 20:03.578
be about you!

20:03.620 --> 20:05.059
Once in a while,

20:05.060 --> 20:06.497
you have to give

20:03.620 --> 20:06.497
someone else the spotlight.

20:06.539 --> 20:07.916
Yeah, I never got

20:07.917 --> 20:09.292
my pizazz on.

20:10.418 --> 20:12.045
I'm so sorry.

20:12.046 --> 20:13.671
I feel just terrible.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.027
And I mean like

20:15.028 --> 20:16.340
Jessie's dancing terrible.

20:17.675 --> 20:18.740
Okay, I was the captain

20:18.741 --> 20:19.803
of that drill team!

20:20.637 --> 20:21.659
Jessie,

20:21.660 --> 20:22.680
this is not about you.

20:24.766 --> 20:27.269
Look, Ber-tootchka,

20:27.270 --> 20:29.771
I realize now that I made

20:24.766 --> 20:29.771
a lot of mistakes,

20:29.813 --> 20:31.564
- but I must've done
- something right,

20:31.606 --> 20:33.316
Because obviously

20:33.317 --> 20:35.026
these kids really love you.

20:35.068 --> 20:36.319
- We do.
- Absolutely.

20:36.360 --> 20:37.403
- Yeah.
- Indeed.

20:37.445 --> 20:38.905
Love is a strong word.

20:40.531 --> 20:42.826
And who loves you the most?

20:43.534 --> 20:46.746
Me, and I always will.

20:46.788 --> 20:48.832
Oh, Mom-moochka!

20:48.833 --> 20:50.875
Oh, Ber-tootchka.

20:50.917 --> 20:52.795
Oh, this is

20:52.796 --> 20:54.671
the longest hug

20:50.917 --> 20:54.671
we've ever had.

20:54.712 --> 20:56.547
- I'm licking icing
- off your shoulder.

20:58.008 --> 20:59.217
Whatever works.

21:00.885 --> 21:03.117
Okay, Ber-tootchka!

21:03.118 --> 21:05.348
Are you ready for

21:00.885 --> 21:05.348
a big dance number?

21:05.389 --> 21:06.557
I guess so.

21:06.558 --> 21:07.725
Why aren't you in it?

21:07.767 --> 21:09.207
Oh, because

21:09.208 --> 21:10.645
a little Bertie told me

21:10.687 --> 21:12.647
- that not everything
- has to be about me.

21:13.982 --> 21:15.566
Good for you, Mom-moochka.

21:17.194 --> 21:18.236
Although I did do

21:18.237 --> 21:19.278
the choreography,

21:19.320 --> 21:21.156
- and the costumes,
- and the make-up, and...

21:21.198 --> 21:22.365
Hit it, Mrs. Kipling!

21:22.406 --> 21:23.574
(GROWLING)

21:23.616 --> 21:25.785
(UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

21:56.691 --> 21:58.651
Happy birthday, Bertram!

21:58.693 --> 21:59.712
- You'd better be
- enjoying this,

21:59.736 --> 22:01.529
- 'cause I think
- I just pulled my hammy.

22:03.281 --> 22:05.096
We hope you like this weird

22:05.097 --> 22:06.910
American dance

22:03.281 --> 22:06.910
old people seem to enjoy.

22:08.619 --> 22:10.184
Ravi, it's rude to call

22:10.185 --> 22:11.748
old people old!

22:11.789 --> 22:13.062
I prefer

22:13.063 --> 22:14.333
country line dancing.

22:14.375 --> 22:15.418
Where's Rascal Flatts

22:15.419 --> 22:16.460
when you need them?

22:18.713 --> 22:20.487
Oh, guys, this is

22:20.488 --> 22:22.259
the best birthday ever!

22:22.300 --> 22:23.301
But did anybody

22:23.302 --> 22:24.302
buy me an actual present?

22:30.474 --> 22:32.393
- Happy birthday.
- Ber-tootchka!

